<subSubSection id="C30C49C9B001D778A0D092F9FBDE7743" pageId="15" pageNumber="198" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA91A42B001D778A0D092F9FBDE7743" blockId="15.[174,1232,1181,1368]" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">
Diagnisis. Medium sized (5.5–10.0 mm) bright colored flies. Frons and face as wide as one eye; vibrissal angles distinctly raised over oral margin, and lunula narrowed downwards; head in profile angular; hind border of head distinctly shortened; proclinate 
<emphasis id="B962C650B001D778A09D9299FF0E776C" box="[174,213,1277,1303]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">orb</emphasis>
numerous, as a group of irregular placed erect setae; Postpedicel 2.0–2.5× as long as pedicel. 
<emphasis id="B962C650B001D778A13C9378FE9B7745" box="[271,320,1308,1342]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">
<emphasis id="B962C650B001D778A13C9378FEF17743" bold="true" box="[271,298,1308,1336]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">{:</emphasis>
f 
<subScript id="17921807B001D778A10B9354FE9B7745" attach="left" box="[312,320,1328,1342]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B962C650B001D778A149937AFE507745" box="[378,395,1310,1342]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">
t 
<subScript id="17921807B001D778A1B09354FE507745" attach="left" box="[387,395,1328,1342]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">2</subScript>
</emphasis>
with ctenidium consisting of long and flattened setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30C49C9B001D778A0D0935AFBA3772C" box="[227,1144,1341,1368]" pageId="15" pageNumber="198" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA91A42B001D778A0D0935AFBA3772C" blockId="15.[174,1232,1181,1368]" box="[227,1144,1341,1368]" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">
Twenty species occur in the south of the Palaearctic and Afrotropical 
<collectingRegion id="49D2D4A0B001D778A4209359FBAF772C" box="[1043,1140,1341,1367]" country="Iraq" pageId="15" pageNumber="198">Regions</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
